===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|hi|हैदराबाद|tr=haidarābād}} / {{bor|en|ur|حیدرآباد|tr=haidarābād}}, from {{m|hi|हैदर}} / {{m|ur|حیدر|tr=haidar|t=lion}} + {{m|hi|-आबाद}} / {{m|ur|آباد|t=-ābād|pos=placename suffix}}. Named in honour of the [[Caliph]] {{w|Ali Ibn Abi Talib}}, nicknamed "Haidar" for his lion-like valour in battles.<ref name="Everett-Heath2005">Everett-Heath, John. ''Concise Dictionary of World Place Names'', Oxford University Press, 2005 p&nbsp;223 ({{ISBN|978-0-19-860537-9}})</ref>

